The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 4: The proposed merger of Air-India and Indian Airlines was put on the fast track today with the A-I board deciding to invite expressions of interest for appointing a consultant for the purpose in the next few days. The board has decided to appoint the consultant in the next four to six weeks to prepare a roadmap for the merger of the two national carriers within 2006-07 without any hiccups, airline sources said.

 Calcutta, May 4: Bata India Ltd will write-off accumulated losses totalling not lower than Rs 40 crore as part of the balance sheet clean-up.

 New Delhi, May 4: The war of words between GSM and CDMA telecom operators on spectrum allocation continued with the Cellular Operators Association of India (COAI) today dismissing reports that subscriber-based allocation was a recent development.

 New Delhi, May 4: The government today assured investors that there would not be any problem regarding the security of payments for the power generated from the proposed seven projects of 4000 mw each.

 New Delhi, May 4: Reliance Petroleum Ltd will list its shares on the bourses on May 10 or 11. Sources said the allotment of shares have been completed.




